<!--
Project-level decision record. ONE FILE PER DECISION. Filename: <slug>.md.

Load-bearing test: only create this when a future audit/health pass would
re-suggest the same thing without this record. Skip ephemeral reasons ("not
worth it now"), self-evident ones, and decisions that fit elsewhere:

  - layer-scoped call → that layer's intent.md `Boundary decisions:` list
  - active rule the codebase must obey → principles.md
  - cross-layer / project-level "we considered X, declined because Y" → here

When a later decision overturns this one: set `status: superseded`,
`superseded_by: <new-slug>`, and leave the file in place. Do not delete.
-->
---
id: <short-slug>
date: YYYY-MM-DD
status: accepted   # accepted | superseded
title: <one-line headline>
related_items: []  # optional list of roadmap ids (e.g. [sk-011])
# superseded_by: <slug>  # required only when status is superseded
---

